## Key Considerations for Remote MCP

When working with Remote MCP servers, developers should consider:

* Authentication and authorization
* HTTPS encryption
* Network latency
* Timeouts
* Rate limiting
* Audit logging
* Server trust and verification
* Data privacy and security

---

## Summary

The Remote MCP workflow follows these steps:

```text
User Request
      ↓
AI Agent understands intent
      ↓
MCP Client lists remote tools
      ↓
Authentication is attached
      ↓
MCP Client calls the selected tool
      ↓
Remote MCP Server executes the request
      ↓
External API returns data
      ↓
Structured result is returned
      ↓
AI Agent generates the final response
```

This workflow illustrates how AI agents securely interact with cloud-hosted tools and external services using the Model Context Protocol (MCP), enabling real-time access to APIs, databases, and enterprise applications.
